# RULE-001: TypeScript Strictness (Critical)

- **No `any`.** Use proper types or `unknown` with narrowing.
- **No `@ts-ignore`** without a `REASON:` comment explaining why and when it can be removed.
- **Explicit return types for exports** — all exported functions and methods must declare their return type.

## Examples

```typescript
// ❌ BAD
export function getItem(id: string) {
  return store.get(id);
}

// ✅ GOOD
export function getItem(id: string): Item | undefined {
  return store.get(id);
}
```

```typescript
// ❌ BAD
// @ts-ignore
const x = legacyApi();

// ✅ GOOD (only when unavoidable)
// @ts-ignore REASON: legacyApi has no types; ticket #123 to add types. Remove after.
const x = legacyApi();
```
